// `bool` is the built-in boolean. It is declared as an enum so it has a nominal
// type identity (and can carry impls/trait impls), but the compiler lowers it to
// a native JS boolean: `false`/`true` are the JS literals, comparisons emit
// `===`, and `if`/`while` use JS truthiness. This module is dependency-free so it
// can always be loaded as a core primitive without pulling in the rest of std.
enum bool {
	false,
	true,
}

use bool::{ false, true };
